

Panda Express is fast, cheap Chinese food, and is known for their signature orangeflavored chicken dish. Panda Express is a chain that is most commonly found in Malls mall food courts, where the prices are less than those found in the Davis location. Similar to the Chinese Buffets in town, the food is premade and served cafeteria style to customers. Panda Restaurant Group, Inc. also owns HibachiSan, which used to share their building. One can smell the oil from Panda Express all over The Marketplace parking lot.

This Panda Express is notably more expensive than its analogous mall locations. A twoentree plate costs $6.25 after taxes.  An Panda Express vs. Davis Noodle City experiment was performed to determine just how cheap their food is, and found that a downtown restaurant that makes food to order, Davis Noodle City, was cheaper by the pound and was arguably quicker if you permit calling in an order ahead of time.

Nothing at Panda Express is vegetarian options vegetarian. Even the mixed vegetables are cooked in chicken broth. Dont bother if youre vegetarian.

Upon purchasing food here, go home and take their online survey.  Upon completion of the survey, you will be given a code that you can use to get a free entree on your next twoentree plate purchase.  They also occasionally offer a free entrée to promote a new dish, such the free Kobari Beef on September 29, 2010.

Panda Express sometimes offers coupons for free items. http://www.pandaexpresssocialmedia.com/uplate/coupon.php?sourcewallpost coupon link

There was a Boston Market in this location years ago.


